I was struggling with setting up the android because of some weird error:
`{"save":false,"callbackId":"not_relevant","pluginId":"SocialLogin","methodName":"login","success":false,"error":{"message":"Cannot find provider 'facebook'"}}`
or
`{"save":false,"callbackId":"not_relevant","pluginId":"SocialLogin","methodName":"login","success":false,"error":{"message":"Cannot find provider 'google'"}}`

The initialize method I was calling:
```typescript
await SocialLogin.initialize({
  google: {
    webClientId: environment.oauth2.client_id,
    iOSClientId: environment.google.iosClientId,
    iOSServerClientId: environment.google.iosClientId
  },
  facebook: {
    appId: environment.facebook.app_id,
    clientToken: environment.facebook.client_token
  },
  apple: {
    clientId: environment.apple.client_id,
    redirectUrl: ''
  }
});
```

Which results to fail because `redirectUrl` is empty and for android this field is required.
I omitted this because we're not interested in apple login on android.

I think you should not throw an error, or at least register Google and Facebook if correct and disable the Apple login.
This costed me a 3 hours of debugging üòÑ

